														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4787259">
									

<p>I certainly get why it could feel that way. Over the course of this short mini-series I'm going to show the operation getting increasingly out of hand, as the Site-19 inventory ranges from the prosaic to the utterly absurd; Dan's standing in the middle of it, getting more and more tired, as the sanity of the situation declines precipitously all around him. Having pretty much the whole thing done, from my perspective the absurdity and grounded character studies are still balanced out by the end. I could have told this story exclusively with the &quot;serious&quot; anomalies on the site, but I wanted to really stretch my muscles and depict the full range of consequences of letting a Site loose. We're not gonna get to do this storyline again for a long while, you know? We'll see if I manage to win you over in the end.</p>
<p>Thank you very much for the compliments, I'm glad you've liked my man Dan so far :D</p>

							</div>

								
					
